me of uncertain origin."]}]},{"name":"Anne","type":"FIRST","meanings":["A name corrpted from Hannah, q.v. It is also found several times in a male name. From Ann, Anne, we have as nicknames Nan and Nancy"],"variants":[{"name":"Nancy","meanings":["Of uncertain origin. From the 18th century it is clearly used as a pet form of   Ann   (  see  Nan  ), but it may originally have been a similar formation deriving from the common medieval given name   Annis  , a vernacular form of   Agnes .  Nowadays it is an independent name, and was especially popular in America in the 1930s, 40s, and 50s."]},{"name":"Nan","meanings":["Originally a pet form of   Ann   (for the initial <i>N-</i>,  compare  Ned  ). It is now also widely used as a short form of   Nancy ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Anne Harington was born in 1457, in Hornby Castle, Lancashire, England. She married Nicolas Eltonhead before 1450, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1490, in Eltonhead, Lancashire, England, at the age of 33."},"et":{"1457–1490":"1457–1490","1451–1496":"1451–1496","1400–1450":"1400–1450","1450–1526":"1450–1526","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1457":"1457","1501":"1501","1478":"1478","1400":"1400","1496":"1496","1451":"1451","1450":"1450","1490":"1490","1526":"1526","Eltonhead, Prescot, Lancashire, England":"Eltonhead, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Eltonhead, Lancashire, England":"Eltonhead, Lancashire, England","Hornby Castle, Lancashire, England":"Hornby Castle, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1457–1490":"1457–1490","1451–1496":"1451–1496","1400–1450":"1400–1450","1450–1526":"1450–1526","1450–1501":"1450–1501","1457":"1457","1501":"1501","1478":"1478","1400":"1400","1496":"1496","1451":"1451","1450":"1450","1490":"1490","1526":"1526","Eltonhead, Prescot, Lancashire, England":"Eltonhead, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Eltonhead, Lancashire, England":"Eltonhead, Lancashire, England","Hornby Castle, Lancashire, England":"Hornby Castle, Lancashire, England"},